He unveils the savoir-faire behind the collection imagined by Virginie Viard with the support of CHANEL's Métiers d'art, including Lesage, Montex, Lemarié, Lognon, Goossens, Maison Michel and Massaro.

The collection is now available in boutiques.

Divided by the symmetry of jewelled buttons and patch pockets, a short-sleeved Peter Pan collar dress in yellow lame chiffon falls in soft tiers and flounces, evoking the play of light in Impressionist paintings.

The CHANEL Fall-Winter 2021/22 Haute Couture collection.
 
See more at chanel.com

Special thanks to Paris Musées and the Palais Galliera.
